==English==

====Etymology====
From the Latin ''-phila'', from the Greek ''philos'', (dear, beloved)

===Suffix===
'''-phile'''
# Used in the formation of nouns and adjectives meaning loving and friendly or love and friend
#: Scott is such a biblio'''phile''', that he won't even put that book down

